&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bank Registered Nurse Band 5&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title: Nurse Band 5&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location/Trust: Stepping Hill Hospital, &lt;/strong&gt;Stockport&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Wards Covered: Ward B4&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pay Rates:&lt;/strong&gt;Band 5*&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you have ambitions to be ‘Outstanding’ in an organisation where you’ll be rewarded by receiving enhanced* Band 5 pay rates?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stockport NHS Trust has been on a fantastic improvement journey. Within just 3 years, they’ve gone from being rated as ‘Inadequate’ by the CQC to being rated as ‘Good’ (with some services rated as ‘Outstanding’), which is a huge achievement, and are on a continuous mission to be rated as ‘Outstanding’ across all areas. This has been, and will be achieved, through the values where ‘everybody matters’.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To get it right, they need the right, highly skilled patient focused workforce throughout the whole process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stockport is a fantastic place to work. A small but friendly and ambitious organisation, living by their values which are demonstrated through their behaviours every day. Passionate about excellent patient care, embracing a culture where staff are listened to and patients come first. Every day these values drive the behaviour and actions for every person in the organisation. Their values and behaviours aren&#39;t just words on a fancy poster; they embody everything they stand for as an NHS organisation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for Band 5 Registered Nurses to join the Staff Bank in order to be part of this continuing mission and ambition to become outstanding - and we’d like you to join them on this journey by becoming part of Stockport.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have flexible Bank shifts and long-term placements available&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Band 5 Pay Rates*:&lt;em&gt;enhanced until 31 January 2021&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Days: £20.00, Nights £26.00, Saturdays £26.00, Sundays £32.00&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Days and Night shifts available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills/Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To apply for this post, you will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have a minimum of 6 months paid experience at Band 5 or 6 level within a hospital in the last 2 years.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comply with NMC Professional Registration and keep up to date with current nursing practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Undertake nursing assessment and evaluation to enable development of appropriate plans of care based on the needs of the individual&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be proficient in the delivery of care to patients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure safe administration of drugs in accordance with NMC and CHS policies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure accurate records are kept in accordance with CHS policy and NMC guidelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return for your hard work commitment NHS Professionals (NHSP) can offer you some fantastic benefits: –&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Competitive Pay Rates&lt;/strong&gt;- work this week, get paid next week!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;First choice of shifts at your Trust&lt;/strong&gt;– Access to shifts before they are available to agency&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Flexible working to suit your lifestyle&lt;/strong&gt;– Take control of when you want to work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build holiday allowance for every shift you work&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Book and manage your shifts on the go&lt;/strong&gt;– Access shifts anywhere, anytime online or through your smartphone&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Support when you need it – 24/7 365 days –&lt;/strong&gt;Call us anytime on 03332 407 552&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stakeholder pension scheme&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
